{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember that we went to-- the play that I'm telling now, I didn't see her perform in that play.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they took me much to the theater.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was, as far as I remember, it was not even a real theater.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was in the house where the firemen had, you know, their house, they used to allow them to make performances.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember that I saw many, many Yiddish shows, like Ansky's And in fact, I was telling my children about the story, because there was a scene that stuck in my mind, in particular, that when one, one who is in that play, calls over the man because-- and says to him, 'Look through the window.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What do you see?' And he said, 'People.' 'Look in the mirror.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What do you see?' He says, 'Myself.' He said, 'It's the same piece of glass.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as soon as there is a little silver on it, you only see yourself.'",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was in reference, because the story was about two friends who started in the yeshiva together, and they pledged-- both wives were pregnant-- that if one has a daughter and one a son, that they're going to be, going to marry each other.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In our tradition, we don't, not allowed to make promises like this, because you cannot make a promise on something that is not born.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's like, you know, like, well, I have a saying. 'The past is history, the present is news, and the future is still unborn.' So you don't give such promises.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it so happened that one has a son and one a daughter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, the one who had the daughter became extremely rich, and he didn't keep his promise.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He completely forgot the promise.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
